comment: Towns (MIN) sets the screen on Nicholson (ORL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Smith (ORL) does not obtain legal guarding position and makes contact with Wiggins' (MIN) body that affects his drive to the basket.
Nicholson (ORL) makes contact with Rubio (MIN) after he has already secured the rebound from a position where he has no reasonable chance to obtain the ball without making contact.
Smith (ORL) sets the screen on Rubio (MIN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Payton (ORL) makes contact with Wiggins' (MIN) arm that affects his driving layup attempt.
Dieng (MIN) maintains legal guarding position and does not affects Fournier's (ORL) RSBQ on the drive to the basket.

After communicating with the Replay Center, the oncourt ruling that Payton (ORL) stepped out-of-bounds by touching the boundary line while in possession of the ball stood because there was no conclusive angle to show that his foot was inbounds.
Towns (MIN) sets the screen on Fournier (ORL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Towns (MIN) makes contact with the ball before it has reached its apex and is still on its upward flight toward the basket.
Towns (MIN) makes contact with Nicholson's (ORL) arm that affects his layup attempt.
Towns (MIN) blocks Nicholson's (ORL) shot attempt prior to any "high-five" contact, which is considered incidental after the block.
[Incidental or immaterial] Incidental contact between Smith (ORL) and Towns (MIN) in transition.
Nicholson (ORL) makes contact with Wiggins' (MIN) body and affects his drive to the basket and layup attempt.
Harris (ORL) makes incidental contact with Wiggins (MIN) that does not affect his shot attempt.
Smith (ORL) maintains legal guarding position as he absorbs the contact from Towns (MIN).
Rubio (MIN) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Fournier (ORL) on the perimeter.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court of a 3 point field goal by Fournier (ORL) was upheld.
Smith (ORL) sets the back screen on Rubio (MIN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Rubio (MIN) makes contact with Payton's (ORL) arm that affects his layup attempt.
Fournier (ORL) maintains legal guarding position and gets his hand on the ball as he defends Wiggins' (MIN) driving shot attempt.
Smith (ORL) makes contact with Towns' (MIN) arm that affects his shot attempt.
Prince (MIN) and Smith (ORL) briefly engage and separate away from the ball.
Oladipo (ORL) legally contests LaVine's (MIN) jump shot.
